\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
If risk-neutral distribution of returns follow the log normal distribution,
 we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\log\mathbb{E}_{t}^{*}(R_{i,t+1})=\mathbb{E}_{t}^{*}(\log R_{i,t+1})+\frac{1}{2}\text{var}_{t}^{*}(\log R_{i,t+1})
\]

\end_inset

Then
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
VIX_{i,t,t+1}^{2} & =2L_{t}^{*}(\frac{R_{i,t+1}}{R_{f,t+1}})\\
 & =\frac{1}{R_{f,t+1}^{2}}\text{var}_{t}^{*}(\log R_{i,t+1})\\
 & \approx\frac{1}{R_{f,t+1}^{2}}\text{var}_{t}^{*}(R_{i,t+1}-1)\\
 & =SVIX_{i,t,t+1}^{2}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

